note.p: This correction is supplied by Cathal Mac Mhuirich himself in the upper margin.
On this form of aer see Ronald Black (1973): 205-06.
Black (1973) gives this as 'fann' but there is clearly a supercript a over the f. I wonder might the missing portion of MS had an i and this might be a form of 'ifern'?
I'm note sure about the HW here.
There are two puncta below the t here, however the present editor would not agree with deleting the t.
This seems to mean including as opposed to something along the lines of 'bestows, conveys, escorts, delivers' given as a translaiton for the verb in eDIL.

Given the scribe's practice so far this is likely to have been intended to be enclosing puncta to indicate the abbreviation. AS is however, the abbreviation has been noted as a single punctum and the abbreviation has been expanded after the g rather than before it.
There is a punctum delens above the suspension stroke here but it is unclear to the present editor how this could fit in here.
